  "text": "LLVM optimization pass pipeline propagation traced through five key components:\n\n1. **PassBuilder** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp` and header `llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h`): The PassBuilder class is the main orchestrator of pass construction. The key method `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline(OptimizationLevel Level, ThinOrFullLTOPhase LTOPhase)` is responsible for constructing the O2 optimization pipeline. This method reads the OptimizationLevel parameter and assembles the appropriate sequence of optimization passes.\n\n2. **PassManager Template** (`llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h`): The core `PassManager<IRUnitT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs...>` template class is the execution engine for all passes. The `run()` method executes the sequence of passes stored in the pipeline, propagating analysis managers and managing pass state and invalidation.\n\n3. **PassBuilderPipelines Implementation** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp`): This file contains the complete implementation of `PassBuilder::buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()`, which assembles module and function simplification pipelines. It includes the logic for building different optimization levels (O0, O1, O2, O3, etc.) and orchestrates the addition of individual passes based on the optimization level.\n\n4. **PassRegistry** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def`): This is a macro-based registry file (using the X-Macro pattern) that defines all standard LLVM passes. Analyses are registered with `MODULE_ANALYSIS` macros, transformation passes with `MODULE_PASS`, `FUNCTION_PASS`, etc. The PassBuilder includes this file multiple times to extract pass metadata for parsing and instantiation.\n\n5. **DeadStoreElimination Concrete Example** (`llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp` and header `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h`): The `DSEPass` class (defined in the header) implements the actual dead store elimination optimization. It contains the `run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM)` method that executes the pass over a function, using MemorySSA and alias analysis to identify and eliminate redundant store instructions.\n\nThe pipeline execution flow is: PassBuilder::buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() → PassRegistry.def (for pass lookup) → PassManager::run() → individual passes like DSEPass::run()"
}

